    "Typically, the interaction potentialfoot_10 V (q) is chosen as the dual or single gatescreened form 16 given by e 2 2ϵ0ϵrq tanh qd sc or e 2 (1-e -2qdsc) 2ϵ0ϵrq respectively, with screening distance d sc ∼ 5 -40 nm and relative permittivity ϵ r ∼ 4 -30 17 [33].",
    "The screening distance d sc is related to the physical gate distance d g via d sc = d g ϵ ⊥ /ϵ ∥, where ϵ ⊥ (ϵ ∥) is the dielectric constant of hBN perpendicular (parallel) to the atomic plane [93].",
    "The value of ϵ r not only encompasses the contribution of the hBN dielectric, but also captures screening and renormalization effects due to the remote bands.",
    "The latter can be accounted for more quantitatively by down-folding methods such as the constrained random phase approximation [158][159][160].",
